00_Black

Relm understood for the first time her position in the world
of mages at the magic academy.

Those who hesitate in understanding what they can
immediately comprehend, and those who abandon understanding.
Those who spend a long time on magic that they can easily
cast. Relm clearly understood that she was a genius when it
came to magic.

Eventually, understanding was replaced by arrogance, and she
began to call herself a genius. Ideally, adults should have
reprimanded her for her arrogance, but there were few who
showed interest in others in all aspects of their
achievements.

Clea, the meddlesome doctor, was the only one who worried
about her, but Relm disliked interference and locked herself
in her room, immersing herself in reading the literature of
the academy. In the end, even though her location had
changed, Relm was still lonely.

Without any equal friends or understanding supporters of her
dreams, and with her elderly mentor who was her last
remaining support having passed away a few years ago, Relm
clung even more desperately to her own dream.

Relm's craving and arrogance towards that cursed-like dream
led her to break the taboo. She went ahead and touched the
book on the manufacturing method of blank grimoires, which
was prohibited from being viewed, without permission.

As punishment, she was deprived of her own refuge, her
knowledge of magic, and as a result, she ended up leaving
the magic academy and gaining an opportunity to rely on
someone else.

This was the beginning for Relm, in the true sense of the
word, of leaping from a small room into a vast world.
